messages.content: Aeolian wakes up in his bed.

I yawn, and arise, checking my notes.

Following this, I head out to my nourishment room to secure nourishment.
Theo is waiting for him in the nourishment room. "Good morning, sir!"

‚ÄúMorning.‚Äù This man is truly the emperor of being in my house. ‚ÄúHope you‚Äôre well.‚Äù I grumble, brewing a Caffeinated Beverage.

> Don‚Äôt even TALK to me before I‚Äôve had my Caffeinated Beverage.
- Wazy Emerson
"Yes, sir." He nods.
‚ÄúMhm. Anything on the itinerary? I agreed informally to meet with Aliza this morning, of course‚Ä¶‚Äù
"I don't believe so, sir! Oh, um... They said we should go to the temple today to speak with Mr Klezmer."

‚ÄúAh, yes, right.‚Äù I sip my beverage.

> I can‚Äôt remember shit that was three weeks ago damn
- Rean Descartes
"You know him well, right sir?"
‚ÄúReasonably. He‚Äôs a kind young lad.‚Äù
"Would he really have anything to do with the emperor‚Äôs attacker, then?"
‚ÄúI don‚Äôt personally think so, but it‚Äôs possible.‚Äù
"So you don‚Äôt believe the high priestess‚Äôs claim?" He makes a mental note of this as someone knocks at the door.
‚ÄúThe claim of the woman who barged in and blew up a building? Not taking it at face value, no.‚Äù I sigh, and open the door.
It‚Äôs Aliza. "Good morning, Ally."
‚ÄúMorning. I had a most unusual dream.‚Äù
"Well, you have always been quite the dreamer." Aliza.

‚ÄúPerhaps so. I am untethered by the limits of many others.‚Äù I shake my head. ‚ÄúThe dream seemed a warning, or a hint‚Ä¶ at any rate, I was next going to speak with the man apprehended yesterday.‚Äù
"Who?"
‚ÄúLocruz Klezmer.‚Äù I answer promptly and without delay.

"Who's that?" Aliza.

"The man who was apprehended yesterday." Theo.
‚ÄúYess. He lives around here. Nice kid.‚Äù
"Why did he get arrested then?" Aliza.
‚ÄúThat is what I wish to discern.‚Äù
"I see." Aliza nods.
‚ÄúWould you like to accompany this endeavor?‚Äù
"If it‚Äôs relevant."
‚ÄúIt should be. Libra seems to believe this already solves everything. And if she‚Äôs just very confidently wrong, understanding why is still useful.‚Äù
"I see." Aliza nods.
I exit my home.
They follow.
‚ÄúIt‚Äôs an absurd overreach of power, regardless of veracity.‚Äù I shake my head, heading over to the indicated location.

They arrive at the temple. The Duchess exits it in front of them. "‚Ä¶Hello, Baron. ‚Ä¶And you would be Washington‚Äôs daughter?"

Aliza nods. "It‚Äôs a pleasure to see you, Duchess."
‚ÄúMrm.‚Äù I abstain from the pleasantries, nodding at her.
"Why are you here?" The duchess.
‚ÄúTo speak with your prisoner.‚Äù

"*My* prisoner?" She chuckles mockingly. "I believe he prefers the term son."

Theo looks confused.

"I suppose these roles are not so different." Aliza speaks wisely, prompting a look of annoyance on the Duchess's face.
‚ÄúWhat.‚Äù

"I suppose you wouldn't understand the trappings of family, Aeolian." Aliza.

"Call it a joke. I have nothing to do with the prisoner here. I was here for my son." The Duchess.
‚ÄúOkay. Great joke.‚Äù
"Hm." The Duchess smirks. "You're not very good at this, are you?" She heads off.
‚ÄúAwkward.‚Äù I enter the building.

They are directed to a large room containing a cell in the center. This room would normally be used for ritual purposes to punish criminals in the name of libra. Locruz is locked inside. Nash Edwardson is guarding him along with 2 other guards.
Nash wakes up, alive once more. An unfamiliar priest, the duchess, and Harriet Dana Edwardson are here.
"Gghh-" He makes a sputtering sound of shock, jerking upwards. "Ah... 'M awake. Alive? Y-eaaaah." He's still a little out of it.

"Welcome back, Nash." The Duchess.

The priest leaves, seeing this was successful.

"Libra has guided your soul back to us." Harriet.
"Er... yes." He says. "Thank you both, for uh, your continued investment." A moment. "In me." He clarifies.
He begins doing the fucking üëâ üëà thing while looking to the side. "Is it customary, um, for those who were revived, to speak of visions?"

"Yes, I would assume hallucinations are common when your brain is being magically pressed back together." The Duchess.

Harriet ignores her, looking at Nash with a serious expression. "You saw the afterlife, then?"
"Something like that, yes." Nash says, staring dazed into the distance, too shaken to even antagonize Harriet as usual.

"I‚Äôve been there once too." Harriet clenches her first, her hand shaking lightly.

The Duchess reacts with a sort of knowing smirk, like she‚Äôs enjoying a good practical joke.

Nash, um... doesn't know what his mother is doing. Is she signaling something to him, maybe...? Looking at her warped smile, like she knows a secret, it's as if he's being mocked. Which is dumb, obviously. He's misreading the situation.

And h-hey, why's Harriet responding like that? All furrowed brow, as if she *understands*... it's not the same. It couldn't have been the same experience, surely. It's not like Harriet, uh, needs.. whatever. Is she mocking him too?
"And what did youuuuu see?" Nash drawls, raising an eyebrow. *Tell me something stupid, or made up! Y-yeah.*

"‚Ä¶" Harriet goes silent and closes her remaining eye. She breathes shakily.

"Yes, I had to save her once too. Unfortunately that eye of hers was unsalvageable for whatever reason. At least your eyes still work, Nash." The Duchess.
"Yes." Nash says proudly. "That's one thing I've still got going for me." He smirks.
"You wear glasses." Harriet scoffs. "I have work for you, Nash."
Nash reaches up to touch his glasses self-consciously, then shakes it off. "Well.. fine. What is it?"
"We‚Äôve captured a member of the hellhounds, the leader of their street gang called Destiny. He‚Äôs working with the emperor‚Äôs attacker. But refuses to tell us who."
Nash scoffs. "And you can't just torture him?"
"‚Ä¶He‚Äôs resilient. Regardless, we‚Äôre using him as bait now. I want you to guard him."
"GUARD him?" Nash says, disbelieving. "From what..? Killing himself?"
"From the actual attacker who will come to save him, Nash. That is what bait means."
"Ohhh, that makes sense."
"I‚Äôll leave you 2 to it, then." The Duchess smiles and leaves.
"Right." Nash says.
He wraps his arms around himself and scowls up at Harriet.
"Your comrades are already watching him. Follow me." Harriet walks down a corridor.
Alright. Sure!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
Urgh. He doesn't even know why he's so mad right now. It's a pointless emotion.
Nash gets up and follows her.

They arrive at a large room containing a cell in the center. This room would normally be used for ritual purposes to punish criminals in the name of libra. Inside is a young man who looks younger than Nash. 

Ruth notices him with a slight smile. Orion rushes over to him. "You‚Äôre back!"

Nash moves to him too. What do you even say in this sort of situation...? *Sorry, I really wanted to die back there. I thought we had all agreed on the importance of that. Why are you happy that I'm here? I shouldn't be happy for that.*
He smiles faintly. "Yes."

"You‚Äôre lucky your parents are rich. I wouldn‚Äôt have the cash for those sorts of resurrection rituals." Orion.

"That thing got away because of your reckless death." Ruth.
Nash allows his smile to become fuller. "Sorry for dying in pursuit of victory, I suppose."

"Pursuit of victory implies that accomplished anything. Grow up." Ruth punches his shoulder. 

"Is this place‚Äôs entire government this batshit?" Teenager in jail.
Nash turns to the kid, rolling his eyes. "What would you know, degenerate?"

"The eclipse totally owns you guys." Teen.

Harriet leaves.
Nash does the get-a-load-of-this-guy point in the kid's general direction, but otherwise ignores him.

"Do you feel like telling us yet who stabbed the emperor?" Ruth.

"I told you it wasn‚Äôt us, you idiots!" Teen.
Nash just laughs. "Stop being moronic. We know it's you."

"Don‚Äôt you guys think this was Linjamin? I mean even ignoring the fact he‚Äôs not that stupid I don‚Äôt even work with him!" Teen.

"So you‚Äôll give us a list of associates you do work with, then?" Ruth.

He shuts up.
Nash leans against the wall, fixing the teen with a stare.
Orion heads over next to Nash. "How was it? ‚Ä¶Dying, I mean."

Nash exhales, looking at his hands. "Um.. a little weird." He says quietly, deliberately trying to keep Ruth and the other teen out of the conversation. "I mean, it's all fuzzy now, but. I really think I saw *Her.*" He tries to inject an appropriate amount of gravitas into the word.
"Your mom?"
Nash blinks. "What? No. Why would I...? I mean my goddess, obviously." *Why would he think that? Hah, what? Huh?*
"Oh‚Ä¶ Libra?"
"Yeah."
"What was she like?"
Nash hesitates. "...Warm. And a little stern. But in a well-intentioned way, I think."
"It was nice." He admits. *Not all of it, obviously. And I didn't like. You know, the going.*
"I‚Ä¶ see."
*Fuck, was that a weird thing to say? I don't think it's weird...! It's a normal response to meeting your goddess. Don't judge me, Oriooooonnnnn....*
Nash crosses his arms. "I was in awe, of course. So we didn't exchange many words." Nash blinks. "How did the situation with the intruders and the.. *creature* resolve itself, after my death?"
"We just kind of ran. Haven't heard anything about it since. The order said they'd look into it though."

"Makes sense." Nash nods. "Well... thanks for retrieving my body, I suppose." *Even if I'd rather you didn't. Haha, why didn't you just leave me behind...? Did you not think that was a suitable death for me?*
"Do you think that thing was... Human?"
He frowns. "I'm not sure. It had a human face, and certainly vocalized, but the proportions, eugh. I really don't know."
"Think it could be one of those mutants?"
Nash's face spasms briefly. "May..be. That kind of savagery would be, uh, *characteristic* of them." *Disgusting.*
"Makes sense. I've never heard of that kind of mutation though."
Nash braces a hand against the bottom of his chin, lost in thought. "Me neither."
At this point, Aeolian enters. ((End session sorry Penny left hours ago and never returned))
‚ÄúMm.‚Äù I acknowledge the existence of someone I have seen in my life before.
"Who are you?" Male guard with Nash.
Nash looks at Burr with disdain.
‚ÄúI‚Äôm Aeolian Burr.‚Äù
Nash waves a hand dismissively. "Yes, yes. What are you *doing* here, is the prudent question."
‚ÄúI came to speak with my acquaintance, who was arrested in an illegal act of terrorism that collapsed a building on those inside. I‚Äôm highly curious what led to such a thing.‚Äù
Nash laughs unkindly. "Why do terrorists do anything? To threaten the structure of society. Those are his motives squared away."
‚ÄúThe act of terrorism was not his. I have no idea of anything at all he has done. Such is part of the question.‚Äù
"What? Then who did it?" Female guard.
I roll my eyes. ‚ÄúThe one who arrested him. The ends justify the means, clearly.‚Äù
Nash tilts his head, confused. "Can you stop saying stupid shit?"
‚ÄúNot in any sense.‚Äù
"Ally, you sound like you can only say stupid shit." The woman with Aeolian.
That is a terrible nickname.
"So what do you propose, then?" Nash drawls. "A complete jailbreak? A miscarriage of justice?"
‚ÄúAttempting a jailbreak here would be absurdly foolish, and justice has already been aborted. I, again, merely intend to speak with him.‚Äù I ignore my friend.
"For what purpose?"

I stare blankly at this man asking what I have spent the past several minutes explaining. 

‚Äú‚Ä¶To solve the mystery.‚Äù
"The mystery is solved."
"He's a terrorist."
‚ÄúNo.‚Äù
"Yes."
‚ÄúThat is not a solution.‚Äù
"How is it not."
‚ÄúIt does not have any backing or answer anything.‚Äù
"It does."
‚ÄúHow.‚Äù
"He's a terrorist."
‚ÄúWhat is the backing for that or answers it provides.‚Äù
"He's in jail."
‚ÄúNot an answer to either.‚Äù

"To be clear, I run a street gang. That‚Äôs not terrorism." Locruz.

The female guard hits the bars, silencing him implicitly.
Nash crosses his arms, leaning against the wall behind him. "Still a crime." Probably.
‚ÄúGlad to hear something from you, at least‚Ä¶‚Äù I sigh. ‚ÄúThis is almost wholly unrelated to the purported reason he was taken in.‚Äù

A flash of annoyance crosses Nash‚Äôs face. ‚ÄúWhy does this matter to you‚Ä¶? He‚Äôs a threat to the crown. The specific *crime* might be debatable, I‚Äôll acknowledge that, but he‚Äôs still in jail for a reason.‚Äù
‚ÄúBecause I care about truth, and reason, and the reasons for things.‚Äù
‚ÄúUghhhh.‚Äù Nash says, face contorting. ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt know why you‚Äôre pretending it makes you a noble truth seeker or whatever to endlessly squabble over technicalities.‚Äù
‚ÄúThey are not mere technicalities. And no, I am not a noble truth-seeker for this reason. This is hardly worth my time.‚Äù
‚ÄúOkay, then leave?‚Äù
‚ÄúNo.‚Äù
‚ÄúYes.‚Äù
‚ÄúNot your decision to make.‚Äù
Nash turns to his boss. ‚ÄúRuth, make him leave.‚Äù
"‚Ä¶We don‚Äôt have that authority, Nash." The female guard who is named Ruth sighs and crosses her arms. "If we let him talk to the prisoner we might learn more too."
‚ÄúUgh‚Ä¶‚Äù Nash mutters. ‚ÄúAnd what if he tries something?‚Äù *Idiot. Obviously he wouldn‚Äôt. And you‚Äôre here to prevent that, so you‚Äôd just have to do your job. Moron.*
"Then we‚Äôll have grounds to stop him." Ruth.
‚Äú‚Ä¶‚Äù
‚ÄúIndeed.‚Äù
"...Whatever."
"Do what you want."
‚ÄúMm. Are you alright, Locruz? Relatively speaking.‚Äù
"No." He sighs. "I'll say this much, though. We didn't have anything to do with that whole assassination attempt. Like, us hellhounds as a whole."
*Yeah, right.* Nash thinks.
‚ÄúUs‚Ä¶ hm. Is the organizational structure not such that such a thing could happen without your knowledge?‚Äù

"It *could* happen without me hearing. But it just wouldn't. I wasn't even hanging around hellhound guys when I got arrested. But it'd be even less possible for those guys to do it. It's all nonsense!"
‚ÄúInteresting. But you don‚Äôt deny an affiliation with them. Do you know what exactly the priestess was suspecting, then?‚Äù
"Not really. She didn‚Äôt listen to anything I was saying! She, uh‚Ä¶ Well I shouldn‚Äôt really be talking about this‚Ä¶ She‚Äôs kind of got her biases about us."
Nash listens to this conversation with trepidation.
‚ÄúI can imagine. What were you doing at that time? At‚Ä¶ the Major‚Äôs, right?‚Äù

"Uh‚Ä¶ Well, at around the same time the emperor was stabbed, some monster killed a bunch of my guys! The major was a witness. I dunno what happened with that though, since he decided to test us for the info and he threw me out of his window."
‚ÄúA monster‚Ä¶?‚Äù
"Yeah. That‚Äôs what I said."
‚ÄúYyess. What sort?‚Äù
"I didn‚Äôt see it."
‚ÄúOh.‚Äù
"Yeah."
‚ÄúWho did? ‚Ä¶the major, I guess‚Ä¶‚Äù
"‚Ä¶Yeah."
‚ÄúRight.‚Äù I nod. ‚ÄúI guess for the reasoning behind your arrest, I‚Äôd have to speak to‚Ä¶‚Äù I hold my head. ‚ÄúAaaagh‚Ä¶‚Äù
"Umm... But is this really relevant to anything, boss?" Aeolian's male follower.
‚ÄúYes‚Ä¶? Well, it may be a red herring‚Ä¶‚Äù
(( @Don'tAtmey @Don'tAtmey @Don'tAtmey ))
"A red herring?"
‚ÄúPerhaps the belief that he has anything to do with the king‚Äôs assassination attempt is merely delusion, conjured based on nothing at all.‚Äù
"I meant the monster."
‚ÄúYess.‚Äù
"Huh?"
‚ÄúYes, that matter may not be related.‚Äù
"I‚Äôd still like to learn more." The woman who called Aeolian Ally.
‚ÄúWell, alright. It is a curious event, certainly. Where did this occur?‚Äù
Locruz gives the address.
‚ÄúCurious indeed‚Ä¶ don‚Äôt let me interrupt you, obviously, if you have any questions, Aliza‚Ä¶‚Äù
"Well, I‚Äôd rather see this fit myself." Aliza just walks out.
‚Äú???????‚Äù I look around. ‚ÄúWell. Sorry about this. I‚Äôll see to getting you a more proper legal defense, hopefully‚Ä¶‚Äù
"We‚Äôve got it handled." Ruth.
‚ÄúWho are you.‚Äù
"Captain Ruth Wayne. We work for the imperial guard."
‚ÄúMmyeh.‚Äù I shrug, and looking over at Locruz and then Nash, who I don‚Äôt know is named that, follow after Aliza.
Ruth steps out of earshot from Locruz. "What did you 2 think of his story?"
Nash sticks out his tongue like a petulant child.
"Huh?‚Äù Orion.

Nash just crosses his arms, staring at the ground. He feels.. taken off-guard. Abandoned. *Not a normal emotion to have. Or response, in any way.* "He's obviously just.. making things up to escape guilt, isn't he?" *Don't look for someone to affirm your responses!*
"Partly. But I do believe him about the monster. I think it‚Äôs the same one we met last night." Ruth.

"Perhaps." Nash says, worrying his bottom lip. *Urgh. Unwilling to concede anything, as usual. You just haaave to let eeeeeveryone know that. It's so obvious you've been outwitted, in some concrete way that's visible to everyone else, and now the country is in danger, and you can't do anything about it! Your world will be.. plundered, violated, and you cannot protect her! How cruel, how cruel...*
"That means Baron Burr might get too close to that monster." Ruth smirks. "That wouldn‚Äôt be too great a loss."
"That's true." Nash says, calming himself. "What a pathetic man."
"Do you know him?" Orion.
"Not personally." Nash scoffs. "But he showed up a while back harassing my family in pursuit of information. Vile."
"We‚Äôll solve this case far earlier than he will." Ruth.
"Yes.." Nash says. "Yes, that's right. So there's nothing to worry about."
*Won't you tell me there's nothing to worry about?*
"There‚Äôs nothing to worry about." Orion nods.
*Ggh... Okay, I guess it can come from you. I guess.*
"Don‚Äôt be stupid." She slaps them both on the side of the head. "You should never stop worrying that easily."
"Ouch, ouch ouch ouch..." Nash whines, covering his head.
"Don‚Äôt be a baby."
Nash just makes a mumbling discontented noise.
((End session sorry))
((that‚Äôs fine))
(( @Don'tAtmey atmeyyyyy))
((I‚Äôm waiting.))
((For me???))
((bash nutton..))
A woman(?) whom Nash would not recognize at all but whom is undoubtedly the one known as "Selle" approaches.
Selle wakes up in a chair at an unfamiliar table. Donald is distracted reading a book across from him.

*Ugh... What the hell was that dream...*
Selle is alert to the fact that they are in a completely unfamiliar place, and sitting at a table. 
*Where the hell am I? I fell asleep on Laura's couch. I must have been dragged somewhere while I was asleep.*
Selle notices that Donald is across from them.
"Ugh... What's going on here?"
"Morning." Donald tosses aside the Wazy Emerson book. "The boss wants to speak with you and that fixer of yours made me carry you instead of waking you up. Kooky bitch."

*Really not the best experience waking up somewhere other than where you fell asleep. That dream must have put me in a real deep sleep for me to not wake up being carried. Setting that aside, the boss? I guess I'll see what happens.*
"Yeah, sure. I'll speak with him."
"Just don‚Äôt set him off, okay? He *will* kill you and then I‚Äôll have to be the one to clean up your mess."
"Haha... I'll do my best."
"The Queen of the Night and the leader of the Faceless will be there too. Are you familiar with them?"

*What's with the high ranking entourage? The Queen of Night especially is someone who is incredibly difficult to find out any information about. Definitely not a good sign. I can't exactly refuse though.*
Selle breathes a deep sigh.
"Yeah, I'm familiar with them."
*I guess I'll find out why they're all here soon.*
Donald gets up. ‚ÄúAlright, follow me.‚Äù

*Where the hell are we, anyway? This is so fishy...*
Selle stands up and follows Donald, looking around and trying to understand where they are in the meantime.
((Roll perception ig))
(Bruh. Nat1
Selle has no idea if they‚Äôre even still in Soltaria.

They enter a large room. There are 4 chairs, seemingly one for each leader of the hellhounds. The 2 leaders Donald mentioned are seated at their respective spots. At the back of the room is a large throne of a pitch black colour, seemingly constructed out of weapons that have been welded together. The Endless Eclipse rests on it.

Donald gives a polite bow and takes his own seat.

*Wow this is definitely not intimidating at all yeah... What kind of place even is this? How do you make this and have people just not know it exists. I have way too many questions. I just need to follow what's going on, I suppose.*
Selle bows, visibly a little confused. They look around the room and try to discern the mood of everyone.
The Eclipse leaves his throne and approaches Selle. "Yule, correct? I am the undying man known as the devil of Soltaria."

*Friendlier than expected.*
"Yes, I am Yule. It's a pleasure to meet you."
"Tell me what happened to my boy, Locruz."

*Locruz... Laura told me what happened to him... I'm glad he's alive.*
Selle starts to recall their memories and say what happened.
"Yesterday, I went with him and one other person to investigate what had happened to Destiny's members. We were told that the person with the most information about what happened was Major Iono Wilkinson. Locruz led us to his house and the Major told us to fight him to get the information we needed. During the fight, Locruz was knocked out onto the street and was unconscious. Apparently, Iono had tipped off the church that we were there and sent Harriet Dana Edwardson and a group of priests to try and... subjugate us. Myself and another person had to use a spell to escape, but Locruz was far from us and wasn't conscious. Only yesterday had I heard that Locruz is fine but being held by the Order. That's the extent of my knowledge."
*That kid... always getting into the worst situations. Damn it.*
"Ha." He grabs Yule‚Äôs shoulder with a terrifyingly firm hand. "You‚Äôre well-informed. I don‚Äôt need to explain why that‚Äôs a problem, do I?"

*Guh... What a pain... Maybe I need to cut down on the explanations sometimes...*
Selle face twitches a bit.
"...Kgh... What are you getting at?"
"You‚Äôre going to bring him back to us. Or I‚Äôll kill you right now." The Eclipse chuckles happily.

*The snowball just keeps rolling down the hill. Everything is always fucking trouble.*
Selle winces.
".......Fine."

"Good. Do whatever you want to bring him back, just keep us out of it. No relying on Donald‚Äôs poor joke at generosity." The Eclipse.

"Sir, I have a question for him as well." The Queen smirks.

*Keep them out of it, huh.*
Selle looks towards the direction of the Queen, waiting for the question.
*Probably the most frightening person here. There's not much I know about her, compared to everyone else.*

"I don‚Äôt believe for a second you stabbed the emperor. You‚Äôd have the most to lose from his replacements, wouldn‚Äôt you?" The Queen smiles as she approaches. "No‚Ä¶ The emperor you attacked‚Ä¶ It was the acting emperor, wasn‚Äôt it? That‚Äôs the error in the high priestess‚Äôs divination. Am I wrong?"

"I shouldn't be surprised that you know so much. Divination? Sounds like a whole bunch of shit. Of course it's wrong. I don't even know who killed the Emperor... In other words, you are absolutely correct."
Selle grimaces in disgust and looks away as she remembers Asturian's  face.
*Scary lady. She knows everything. But, this gives me a lot of information. Someone's put "Selle"'s face out there as the killer of the Emperor. Poor book publishing companies.*

"To be clear, uh‚Ä¶ That wasn‚Äôt us either. Even Linjamin‚Äôs not that stupid. If anyone here knows anything, it‚Äôs the queen and she‚Äôs not talking." Donald.

Linjamin remains silent.

"You were at the party too, weren‚Äôt you Yule? I know what Asturian‚Äôs attacker looks like‚Ä¶ And I saw him at the party too." The Queen.

*Feels weird for someone to refer to me in 3rd person...*
"There's no point beating around the bush with you. Yes, I was at the party."

"Huh!?" Donald.

"That‚Äôll be all." She sits back down smugly.

*No matter what I said, I was only confirming information she already knew anyway.*
Selle sighs and shakes her head.

Linjamin gets up. "Is everyone done then?"

Donald and the queen nod.

"Go ahead, Linjamin." Eclipse.

*This is really turning into a straight up interrogation now.*
Selle is alert.

"Sorry, but we can‚Äôt let you know the route here." Linjamin grabs Selle‚Äôs face with shocking speed and magically knocks them out.

Selle wakes up in a garbage dump in the slums of the city. Their head hurts.

"Ugh..."
*At least it's over. Could have picked a better place to stick me in, though.*
Selle feels their arm in immense, burning pain, paired with a massive headache. They wince in immense pain and feel that that arm has lost feeling. Before Selle can even acknowledge their surroundings, they grab an emergency pill from their inner vest pocket and swallow it.
*I went way too long without medicine. So much time spent unconscious is bad... and this place stinks.*

*Locruz... I guess he would probably be held at the main church in Soltaria... What would they even be doing with him? Laura joked about converting him to be a youth pastor or something but they are probably just trying to use him to get information about me.*
Selle stands up and looks around.
No one seems to be around. It's a very secluded spot.

*They know my face. I need to create a disguise, and a new name.*
Selle reaches into their inventory to take out a disguise kit. It contains make-up, hair dye, and various coloured contact lenses. This is what they used to create the "Selle" disguise.
*Maybe a young lady would be a good disguise. It would be, the easiest... As for a name, I'll pick something familiar, and simple. Something like, Elyssa. It's close enough to my real name but not so much that it's the same. I can use a blonde wig, and wear brown contacts. The only thing I need is a change of clothes and a bath.  I only have this black jacket at the moment, but I've got 15 gil to my name. Should be feasable.*
They have applied the contacts and let their hair down instead of tying it up, but have decided to not put the wig on yet. They still have a very androgynous appearance.
After this, Selle tries to figure out which part of the slums they are in and how far they are from a clothes dealer and an inn.
They can go to those places without much issue. Though it would be a clothes store and not a clothes dealer, which sounds like a crime somehow.
Selle brushes themselves off and heads towards an inn.
